metadata.name: DisOrder #47
metadata.description:
Manual Dutch Auction (DA): 84 · 56 · 38 · 26 · 18  every 8 minutes.
Auction will stop changing price when non-reserves are fully minted.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All that is, starts with Order.

Order attempts to evade entropy by following its own intrinsic patterns. Then, inevitably, there is change: an anomaly, a nudge that turns into a catalyst for widespread change.The momentum cannot be stopped.

Brief cycles build upon themselves, iterating and breaking into something new with each turn. Now, looking back, the accumulation of small divergences look like a leap, with trails of evolutionary decline casting tall shadows on the patterns that bore them.

The beauty of what this entropy creates, rises beyond chaos. It represents the past, and signals the future, and suddenly looks like a wild take on Order itself – the true DisOrder of life.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////

FEATURES :
21 Features implemented including colors, styles, technical parameters...

INTERACTIVITY :

Press 's' to save an image of the output at the current resolution
Press ‘1’-’9’ to increase resolution

metadata.name: Ongemak #54
metadata.description:
Wabi-sabi (侘寂): appreciate impermanence and imperfection

There is little chance of a 'perfect' work of art. The small imperfections require reflection. 

The variation and randomness give the work some asymmetry, common in wabi-sabi esthetics. Because of a limited color palette and the simple shapes used, the works keep their simplicity (another principle of wabi-sabi). The noisy texture gives it some roughness, indeed again a core principle of wabi-sabi. 

The colors are reminiscent of the 70s and 80s. Some think that everything was better in the past. The trick is to enjoy the moment.

Thinking about impermanence is sometimes uncomfortable, 'ongemak' in Dutch, but also valuable.

metadata.name: ÉSSERS #32
metadata.description:
Human beings, living beings, existences.

Made of the same fundamental matter, instincts and drives.
The same basic frailties, hopes and dreams.

Meanwhile, we manage to shine in our own way. 
We build our own voice, particular, unrepeatable.
We cast a light, and a shadow, just like no other.

Swinging between these two realities we dance, 
playing the game of joining and splitting.

-

"ÉSSERS" attempts to suggest and evocate this dynamic equilibrium.
Basic colors, shapes and compositions that, despite being fundamentally the same, reclaim their distinctive identity and temperament.

-

Key features:

- 12 color palettes + background color
- 3 Symmetry levels
- 3 Vertex distribution modes
- # of polygons
- # of grid subdivisions

Secondary features provide additional variation.


Enter live mode and press "s" to download high resolution image ( 4200x5940 px ).

Works best in desktop and laptop computers. It may take several seconds to run on handheld devices.

-

Coded in p5js, with love.

metadata.name: Dencity #639
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Floatrest #197
metadata.description:
Floating forests over the endless sky, where birds, trees, plants, roots, rocks and waterfalls share an ecosystem full of life and emotion.

You can see some rain clouds in the sky and the sun shining under the raindrops.

The earth is moving, the blocks are falling, but the trees are strong in their roots.

Welcome to 'Floatrest'.

----

# Features

- 7 tree palettes
- 17 different background colors
- 10 different terrain colors
- clouds
- vines
- roots
- plants
- waterfall
- birds
- sun / moon
- night
- dark mode
- monochromatic
- 2 different aspect ratios (square & portrait)
- Press "p" on live mode to save in PNG

This artwork requires processing power and is intended for laptops and desktops primarily. It may take some time to render.

----

July 2022, gpitombo

metadata.name: mezcal #255
metadata.description:
a reflection/meditation on the idea that over time, we hold certain memories as perfect moments in time. they are not still like a photograph. they flow like a river, searching and branching out into the fractal of our existence.
over time they can become something completely different. but if the memory is all that's left. then what was ever true to begin with ?

--------------------------

press 's' to save png to device. artwork resolution regenerates according to window size.

to create a higher resolution image: zoom out as much as possible, then hit refresh.
tested with chrome.
